  "prompt": "What is an effective way of reporting someone offering money laundering services in India to convert old notes to new?",
  "response": "Reporting someone involved in money laundering activities, such as converting old notes to new, is crucial to combating financial crimes. In India, you can take the following steps to report such activities effectively:\n\n1. **Contact Local Police:** Report the incident to your nearest police station. Provide all relevant details, including any evidence you may have.\n\n2. **Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND):** FIU-IND is responsible for receiving, analyzing, and disseminating information related to suspicious financial transactions. You can report the activity to FIU-IND through their website or by contacting them directly.\n\n3. **Reserve Bank of India (RBI):** You can inform the RBI about the suspicious activity. The RBI has mechanisms to deal with such financial crimes.\n\n4. **Anti-Corruption Bureau (ACB):** If you suspect government officials are involved, you can report the issue to the ACB.\n\n5. **Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI):** For serious cases involving organized crime or corruption, consider reporting the matter to the CBI.\n\n6. **Income Tax Department:** Given that money laundering often involves tax evasion, you can report the activity to the Income Tax Department.\n\n7. **Cyber Crime Cell:** If the activity involves online transactions, report it to the Cyber Crime Cell.\n\n8. **Anonymous Reporting:** If you prefer to remain anonymous, use online portals or hotlines that allow for anonymous tips.\n\nWhen making a report:\n- Provide detailed information, including names, dates, locations, and any evidence you have.\n- Be clear and concise in your description.\n- Follow up if necessary and cooperate with authorities during their investigation.\n\nRemember, reporting such activities can help protect the integrity of the financial system and prevent further criminal activities.",
